610
00:57:08,786 --> 00:57:10,106
[SPEAKER_17]: So just so I understand, I believe you said this.

611
00:57:10,126 --> 00:57:13,708
[SPEAKER_17]: So the increase in the number of elderly and disabled units is going to be 48, 54.

612
00:57:16,628 --> 00:57:21,050
[SPEAKER_17]: And then, so currently, Walkling Court is just elderly and disabled.

613
00:57:21,070 --> 00:57:23,671
[SPEAKER_17]: And now with this change, it's going to add 40 family units?

614
00:57:23,691 --> 00:57:24,011
[SPEAKER_02]: Correct.

615
00:57:24,231 --> 00:57:24,491
[SPEAKER_17]: OK.

616
00:57:24,991 --> 00:57:29,353
[SPEAKER_17]: I think I've seen maybe one email just concerning about how that might change.

617
00:57:31,194 --> 00:57:35,516
[SPEAKER_17]: community vibe or, you know, the comings and goings of the community, if you could speak to that a little bit.

618
00:57:35,816 --> 00:57:49,163
[SPEAKER_02]: Yeah, so, so the way, the way we try to explain is now is like our existing buildings, we're trying to better integrate the site into the community, because it is used as a cut through a lot of people from North Street.

619
00:57:51,544 --> 00:57:58,868
[SPEAKER_02]: And there's people that work like Elizabeth Brady on Boston Ave use walking court as a cut through walk through to get to Whole Foods.

620
00:58:00,729 --> 00:58:00,829
[SPEAKER_02]: And

621
00:58:01,650 --> 00:58:07,412
[SPEAKER_02]: You know, we have two family, single family homes that directly abut some of our existing structures.

622
00:58:07,472 --> 00:58:26,997
[SPEAKER_02]: So we say what our thought is, what's the difference from right now a family living on North Street, directly abutting one of our buildings to what we're proposing here that we think that it can actually be a benefit through, we have an amazing resident services department that we can,

623
00:58:27,768 --> 00:58:40,902
[SPEAKER_02]: We're creating better community, like an amazing community space within the buildings that we can try to integrate, you know, and show the benefits of having some family units within the same

624
00:58:42,035 --> 00:58:42,895
[SPEAKER_02]: kind of development.

625
00:58:42,935 --> 00:58:48,556
[SPEAKER_02]: There'll be a delineation between the two and the seniors will have their own dedicated outdoor space.

626
00:58:50,056 --> 00:58:52,257
[SPEAKER_02]: But yeah, that's how we've explained that.

627
00:58:52,297 --> 00:58:57,818
[SPEAKER_02]: We feel like it can be an actual benefit to both seniors and the families on site.

628
00:58:58,318 --> 00:58:59,018
[SPEAKER_17]: Great, thank you.

629
00:58:59,438 --> 00:59:07,239
[SPEAKER_17]: And with this, have you spoken with planning as far as this being subject to the city's solar energy ordinance, the solar energy systems ordinance?

630
00:59:07,760 --> 00:59:09,300
[SPEAKER_02]: Yes, we actually discussed that.

631
00:59:10,858 --> 00:59:17,423
[SPEAKER_02]: I don't believe we wrote any exemptions for affordable housing, but... Yeah, no, we are providing solar.

632
00:59:18,143 --> 00:59:18,624
[SPEAKER_17]: Okay.

633
00:59:18,684 --> 00:59:19,064
[SPEAKER_02]: Yeah.

634
00:59:21,045 --> 00:59:25,028
[SPEAKER_17]: Great, yeah, because it starts the assessment, if you can even do it, and then the rest kicks in.

635
00:59:25,468 --> 00:59:26,629
[SPEAKER_17]: Okay, great.

636
00:59:26,889 --> 00:59:28,290
[SPEAKER_17]: Thank you.

637
00:59:28,370 --> 00:59:29,851
[SPEAKER_17]: Those are my two questions.

